Construction firm Group Five said on Friday it will allow a  offer from Greenbay Properties to lapse at 1500 GMT, sending it’s shares down more than 11%. On Monday, Greenbay offered to buy the Group Five’s European assets and gave it until October 20 to accept the offer, which the firm said undervalued its assets compared with possible rival bids. Shares in Group Five tumbled 11.20% to R11.10 after the announcement. 